kaitaka
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a fine cloak or cape woven from finest flax fibre, bleached, with taniko border, a Maori cloak [Maori].
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
