Quote:   ... this gay [Maori] damsel ... knew how to set off her charms to advantage; for, over a European dress, she had retained her native ornaments, and wrapped herself coquettishly in a beautiful kaitaka, ... [fn] <i>E kaitaka</i> is the finest kind of dress, made of the <i>phormium tenax</i>, or New Zealand flax; it is highly valued, and is ornamented with a richly embroidered border, in vandyke patterns, from one to two feet in depth.
